ex2. Rental management system

 We have 3 layers: 
  1. Presentation : regards user interaction
					contains page controller for each template view
					
  2. Domain Logic : structured as a web of interconnected classes: DOMAIN MODEL
					contains Mappers
					entity for each DV table
					Servicers: actual domain logic
					

  3. Data access: done through table data gateway => a gateway for each DB table handling all rows(CRUD methods)
  
  Advantages: it is simple(easy to implement, intuitive), it is consistent(same structure always), and all the objects are kept togheder, easy to find and change things.
  
  Disadvantages: the project is hard to scale, uses cases are difficult to determine and there is no dependency inversion
  
  Factory pattern can be useful for this application in order to handle different types of users or different types of rental cases.
  Also Decorator pattern maight be userd if we want to add special cases to the rentals (fuel included, large period of time.. add discounts based on this extra factors)